1. *Dolje* u selu ima malo ljudi. (Down in the village there are few people.)
2. On je otišao *dolje* u grad. (He went down to the city.)
3. Uspon je bio težak, ali je silazak bio brži i lakši *dolje*. (The ascent was tough, but the descent was faster and easier down.)
4. Očekivali smo da će se polako spustiti *dolje*. (We expected it to slowly go down.)
5. Promenio je smer i pošao *dolje* nizbrdo. (He changed his direction and went downhill.)
6. Krenuli smo *dolje* nizbrdo. (We started going down the hill.)